	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jan 29th 3:05 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hello!<br>I just made level 10 after dying about five or six times in a row (I think the game does that just to keep you playing) ), and I was happy to hit the double-didgits. The problem is, I am in Rivervale, and I made my previous few levels off Goblins and their Warbeads. Trepidation suddenly strikes me as I kill several goblins, loot their corpses, and then realize that there was no little yellow line of text reading, "You have gained experience!" What should I do? I can kill giant spiders and giant wasps I suppose, but they are rare in the Misty Thicket, and whenever I find one, there are others, waiting to ambush me with their despisngly mean AGRO tactics. What should I do? I have read some posts about "Where to Hunt". Most of them are level 30+, so they weren't useful. I asked some players online and they said that the Commonlands were good for a level 10 Druid. I also read that the Qeynos area and the Plains of Karana were excellent hunting grounds, but is that true? Either way, I don't know what to do for hunting. One last thing: I don't have a lot of pp (I actually have about 23 or so, but I am saving it up for something (I am not quite sure what yet)), and I have already bought Light Healing, Strength of Earth, Thistlecoat, and Shield of Thisltes. My strategy as a Druid is mainly defensive. I have no DD spells memorized, actually, the only offensive one I have is Flame Lick (I love that spell!). I have Whirly Wind, yet I don't use it anymore, so I forgot it to make room for my impressive array of Buffs. As for combat, I always buff myself up really big (all my buffs except Shield of Thistles because it is too much mana for too little time) and beat the goblin or whatever into the ground. I absolutely do NOT want Ignite, since I don't hardly ever use DD spells. What about Flaming Fists? I have a FS Warhammer and I am always in the front lines, often as good if not better than a fighter of the same level. So, to save those of you kind enough to read my post, I will summarize my two questions here:<br>1. Where should I (halfling Druid) hunt as at level 10?<br>2. What spells should I buy (the level 9 spells)?<br><br>Thanks a lot,<br>Faerlon<br>10th Druid<br>Tholuxe Paells<br>All around cool guy<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
